The paper deals with the problem of computing all the best swap edges of a tree spanner, which involves exploiting the structure of shortest paths in a graph. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Networked and Online Social Networks (cs.NE), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), or Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. However, since the focus is on graph algorithms and optimization, cs.DS and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also possible, but less likely, as they are more specialized and may not cover all aspects of the paper.
